<subSubSection id="8E6EA9329DD610AE01C36EE4177C7B70" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="98" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="4E04970376C16B53DCE9182E2739BAFA" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="79212C10EDF78A3D3D53E0F0CA97DFAD" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
<taxonomicName id="0DAB2A8577EA0ECD0B4FE13355A6C190" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Madaglymbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madaglymbus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F9BC04795702E4456D165086F76CA84E" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Madaglymbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was erected for the Madagascar species of 
<taxonomicName id="BF0E3EF3FB8D65581B5D917D61815B32" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Aglymbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aglymbus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="171E08C3D09CC7523DF665E1A6758C14" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Aglymbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sharp, 1880 by 
<bibRefCitation id="08DE5706ACF738CD0FBD1CC7C2AD4560" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1017/S1477200007002599" author="Shaverdo, HV" journalOrPublisher="Systematics and Biodiversity" pageId="21" pageNumber="110" pagination="43 - 51" refId="B25" refString="Shaverdo, HV, Monaghan, MT, Lees, DC, Ranaivosolo, R, Balke, M, 2008. Madaglymbus, a new genus of Malagasy endemic diving beetles and description of a highly unusual species based on morphology and DNA sequence data (Dytiscidae: Copelatinae). . Systematics and Biodiversity 6: 43 - 51" title="Madaglymbus, a new genus of Malagasy endemic diving beetles and description of a highly unusual species based on morphology and DNA sequence data (Dytiscidae: Copelatinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1017/S1477200007002599" volume="6" year="2008">Shaverdo et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
. After 
<bibRefCitation id="3D92892EEE0BA2F0FD4771CA47FDB3BD" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" refId="B22">Ranarilalatiana et al. (in press)</bibRefCitation>
transferred two 
<taxonomicName id="E32C5ABE65EC01E8C37DE45313B28CA6" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copelatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="19F2EF33EA52AC2E592A2EBEA6C95EC2" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Copelatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species to 
<taxonomicName id="0C6897BC5E577025B8B1DAED59A2B03B" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Madaglymbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madaglymbus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D529FDD6133C059B8367083AD83E35F0" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Madaglymbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and including the three species described below, fifteen species and one subspecies are currently known from Madagascar and Comoros (see checklist below and 
<bibRefCitation id="7A57E0CD879030F6059D5E08C757FA41" author="Nilsson, AN" journalOrPublisher="Nature" pageId="21" pageNumber="110" publicationUrl="http://www.waterbeetles.eu/documents/W_CAT_Dytiscidae_2019.pdf" refId="B21" refString="Nilsson, AN, Hajek, J, 2019. . http://www.waterbeetles.eu/documents/W_CAT_Dytiscidae_2019.pdf" url="http://www.waterbeetles.eu/documents/W_CAT_Dytiscidae_2019.pdf" year="2019">
Nilsson and 
<normalizedToken id="C85DCECD8D015B272BD77F71B4A2B705" originalValue="Hájek">Hajek</normalizedToken>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). We are constantly finding new species of this genus when collecting across Madagascar and it is premature to present a preliminary checklist including what is known but yet to be described. Revisionary work has been initiated with collegues and type material of all described species consulted directly or indirectly. The three species described below may not form a monophyletic group within the genus. They are described here in advance of a more complete revision of 
<taxonomicName id="BFAF89CCCAA2F5C3302B2EA47DB3A765" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Madaglymbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madaglymbus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="44B9B6AFE0488B452C316762AD49E37C" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Madaglymbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as enigmatic representatives with the terrestrial habitats where they were collected in common.
</paragraph>
